com.sri.ai.expresso.core

Class DefaultCompoundSyntaxTree

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.sri.ai.expresso.core.AbstractSyntaxTree
      • com.sri.ai.expresso.core.DefaultCompoundSyntaxTree
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CompoundSyntaxTree, SyntaxTree, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<java.lang.Object>

    @Beta
public class DefaultCompoundSyntaxTree
extends AbstractSyntaxTree
implements CompoundSyntaxTree
    A default implementation of CompoundSyntaxTree. It is based on a root object (either a syntax tree or another object) and a list of sub-trees.
    Author:
    braz

      • DefaultCompoundSyntaxTree

        public DefaultCompoundSyntaxTree(java.lang.Object label,
                                 java.lang.Object... subTrees)
        Constructs a syntax tree with given label and sub-trees, copying them for internal use. Objects that are not syntax trees will be wrapped as such, unless a single argument is given and it is a Collection; in this case, a copy of the collection is used for the list of the sub-trees

        Just like SyntaxTree.replaceSubTreesAllOccurrences(Function), but with a flag determining if only the first occurrence should be replaced, a pruning predicate, and a listener and. If ignoreRootTree is true, replacement function is not invoked on root tree.
